Look.

01:32:51.270 --> 01:32:53.270
Didn't we have this last week?

01:32:53.270 --> 01:32:56.270
They make fun of me.

01:32:56.270 --> 01:32:57.270
What's going on?

01:32:57.270 --> 01:32:59.270
Nothing. Jill had a nightmare.

01:32:59.270 --> 01:33:00.270
It wasn't a nightmare.

01:33:00.270 --> 01:33:02.270
There was something under there.

01:33:02.270 --> 01:33:04.270
Jill, we all have nightmares.

01:33:04.270 --> 01:33:06.270
You just can't take them so seriously.

01:33:06.270 --> 01:33:12.810
Go back to bed.

01:33:12.810 --> 01:33:13.810
Gotcha.

01:33:13.810 --> 01:33:14.810
It was you?

01:33:14.810 --> 01:33:19.820
Come on. Don't be such a snitch.

01:33:19.820 --> 01:33:24.960
How did you do that?

01:33:24.960 --> 01:33:26.960
I thought you wanted to find something under the bed.

01:33:26.960 --> 01:33:27.960
You're always looking.

01:33:27.960 --> 01:33:29.960
Why don't you just grow up?

01:33:29.960 --> 01:33:30.960
Me?

01:33:30.960 --> 01:33:32.960
You're the one who's still living in a fairyland princess.

01:33:32.960 --> 01:33:35.960
You're 13 years old. Listen to the radio.

01:33:35.960 --> 01:33:37.960
Go to a concert or something.

01:33:37.960 --> 01:33:39.960
Stop being a kid and maybe you won't be scared

01:33:39.960 --> 01:33:41.960
of boogie men under the bed anymore.

01:33:41.960 --> 01:33:45.780
Sweet dreams.

01:33:45.780 --> 01:33:57.520
Jill, don't do this again.

01:33:57.520 --> 01:34:01.530
Jill was having a rough time.

01:34:01.530 --> 01:34:04.530
Everyone kept telling her to grow up

01:34:04.530 --> 01:34:06.530
and act your age, but she didn't know

01:34:06.530 --> 01:34:08.530
how to grow up any faster.

01:34:08.530 --> 01:34:10.530
And she wasn't exactly sure how kids her age

01:34:10.530 --> 01:34:12.530
were supposed to act.

01:34:12.530 --> 01:34:14.530
I can't wait. Adios.

01:34:14.530 --> 01:34:16.530
Jill, I am not late.

01:34:16.530 --> 01:34:20.070
Why does she always do this?

01:34:20.070 --> 01:34:22.070
I don't know, but if she misses the bus again,

01:34:22.070 --> 01:34:23.070
it's your turn to drive her.

01:34:23.070 --> 01:34:28.470
But I'm not going to be late for work.

01:34:28.470 --> 01:34:41.120
Sorry.

01:34:41.120 --> 01:34:43.120
Why do you do this?

01:34:43.120 --> 01:34:45.120
All I ask is that you get up and out on time.

01:34:45.120 --> 01:34:47.120
Now I'm going to have to drive you to school

01:34:47.120 --> 01:34:49.120
and I'm going to be late for work again.

01:34:49.120 --> 01:34:51.120
I told you I'm sorry.

01:34:51.120 --> 01:34:53.120
Don't ignore me.

01:34:53.120 --> 01:34:55.120
You are going to have to learn some responsibility, Miss.

01:34:55.120 --> 01:34:57.120
Other people live in this house

01:34:57.120 --> 01:34:59.120
and we're getting tired of putting up with your childishness.

01:35:00.120 --> 01:35:11.680
Come on.

01:35:11.680 --> 01:35:13.680
Jill kind of understood why her family was giving her grief,

01:35:13.680 --> 01:35:18.480
but her friends weren't helping much either.

01:35:18.480 --> 01:35:30.240
He's so fine.

01:35:30.240 --> 01:35:33.240
I'd talk to him, but I'd probably drool or something.

01:35:33.240 --> 01:35:39.240
Aren't you guys being kind of obvious?

01:35:39.240 --> 01:35:41.240
We're just looking.

01:35:41.240 --> 01:35:44.240
Yeah, like a couple silly gooses.

01:35:44.240 --> 01:35:47.880
Silly gooses?

01:35:47.880 --> 01:35:49.880
My grandmother says that.

01:35:49.880 --> 01:35:55.240
Did you see that?

01:35:55.240 --> 01:35:57.240
He checked her out. Did he check her out?

01:35:57.240 --> 01:35:59.240
No way. He wouldn't check out a geek.

01:35:59.240 --> 01:36:03.670
Look at this.

01:36:03.670 --> 01:36:05.670
Grim's fairy tales.

01:36:05.670 --> 01:36:07.670
Mother Goose.

01:36:07.670 --> 01:36:09.670
The Sandman and other tales.

01:36:09.670 --> 01:36:14.490
What is with her? Is she like a baby or something?

01:36:14.490 --> 01:36:17.490
Talk about us. We saw you flirt with him.

01:36:17.490 --> 01:36:19.490
I didn't. I had to sharpen my pencil.

01:36:19.490 --> 01:36:24.150
Yeah, right.

01:36:24.150 --> 01:36:26.150
He's coming. He's coming.

01:36:26.150 --> 01:36:28.150
Hey, Jill.

01:36:28.150 --> 01:36:29.150
Hi.

01:36:29.150 --> 01:36:31.150
You have that reading assignment Kelly gave us yesterday?

01:36:31.150 --> 01:36:38.270
I lost it someplace.

01:36:38.270 --> 01:36:40.270
What are you supposed to read?

01:36:40.270 --> 01:36:42.270
Hey, these are really interesting.

01:36:42.270 --> 01:36:44.270
Are you reading these?

01:36:44.270 --> 01:36:47.270
Yeah. No, I have to do a book report.

01:36:47.270 --> 01:36:49.270
On what? Humpty dumpty?

01:36:49.270 --> 01:36:52.270
Hey, Jules. I used to play these when I was a kid.

01:36:52.270 --> 01:36:55.270
Jill plays with them now.

01:36:55.270 --> 01:36:59.060
Get out of here, really.

01:36:59.060 --> 01:37:05.160
Hey, Jill. You forgot your doll.

01:37:05.160 --> 01:37:08.160
Jill knew she was being kind of childish.

01:37:08.160 --> 01:37:12.160
But there was something inside her that didn't want to give up the world of fairy tales.

01:37:12.160 --> 01:37:15.160
Because in all those stories, no matter how bad things got,

01:37:15.160 --> 01:37:17.160
everyone always lived happily ever after.

01:37:17.160 --> 01:37:20.160
And the princess always got the prince.

01:37:20.160 --> 01:37:26.290
I've come to awaken you, Sleeping Beauty.

01:37:26.290 --> 01:37:36.400
It's me. I got this for Halloween and I just wanted to show you.

01:37:36.400 --> 01:37:38.400
You did not. You wanted to scare me again.

01:37:38.400 --> 01:37:40.400
No, really. I didn't mean to.

01:37:40.400 --> 01:37:42.400
Yes, you did. I hate you. I hate all of you.

01:37:42.400 --> 01:37:45.400
I'm sorry. Geez. Don't get so bent out of shape.

01:37:45.400 --> 01:37:47.400
Get out of here. Leave me alone.

01:37:47.400 --> 01:38:08.120
I'm so sweat. I'm gone.

01:38:08.120 --> 01:38:11.120
I'm about wanting to live in a world where dreams come true

01:38:11.120 --> 01:38:14.950
and you can wish on a star.

01:38:14.950 --> 01:38:16.950
I wish I could.

01:38:16.950 --> 01:38:18.950
And I wish everybody would just leave me alone.

01:38:18.950 --> 01:39:09.400
Sorry, but John is...

01:39:09.400 --> 01:39:19.910
Mom? Dad?

01:39:19.910 --> 01:39:31.090
Are you down there?

01:39:31.090 --> 01:39:33.090
John?

01:39:33.090 --> 01:39:39.120
Come out, will you?

01:39:39.120 --> 01:39:40.120
You are such a slime.

01:39:40.120 --> 01:39:43.120
If you think that you're going to scare me again.

01:39:43.120 --> 01:40:04.100
Afraid of the dark?

01:40:04.100 --> 01:40:07.100
Stay in the glow of the couch and stay tuned.

01:40:07.100 --> 01:40:10.100
First, there were video games.

01:40:10.100 --> 01:40:13.100
Then came virtual reality.

01:40:13.100 --> 01:40:17.100
Simulated lifelike perspective that makes you feel like you're there.

01:40:17.100 --> 01:40:22.100
But now there's something that blows virtual reality completely away.

01:40:22.100 --> 01:40:25.100
Actual reality.

01:40:25.100 --> 01:40:29.100
Feel the weight of the ball because you're actually holding the ball.

01:40:29.100 --> 01:40:34.100
Feel the wind as you move because you're actually outside.

01:40:34.100 --> 01:40:39.100
Feel the high-fives because you're actually there.

01:40:39.100 --> 01:40:44.100
Nickelodeon wants you to tune in to the most advanced system ever created.

01:40:44.100 --> 01:40:46.100
Yourself.

01:40:46.100 --> 01:40:48.100
Actual reality.

01:40:48.100 --> 01:40:50.100
Nothing else comes close.

01:40:52.100 --> 01:40:54.100
Dunkaroos is the cookie, John.

01:40:54.100 --> 01:40:56.100
For as much frosting as you want.

01:40:56.100 --> 01:40:58.100
So how do you do your Dunkaroos?

01:40:58.100 --> 01:41:00.100
The super duper deep dunk.

01:41:01.100 --> 01:41:07.780
The lord dainty dunk.

01:41:07.780 --> 01:41:11.780
You can dunk a Dunkaroos in as much chocolate vanilla frosting as you want.

01:41:13.780 --> 01:41:15.780
So how do you do your Dunkaroos?

01:41:15.780 --> 01:41:17.780
The upside down dunk.

01:41:17.780 --> 01:41:25.970
Now the sneaking begins again with Are You Afraid of the Dark?

01:41:25.970 --> 01:43:43.140
This is a dream.

01:43:43.140 --> 01:43:45.140
God be dreaming.

01:43:45.140 --> 01:43:47.140
You're getting warmer but you're only half right.

01:43:47.140 --> 01:43:50.140
This place is a dream but you're not dreaming.

01:43:50.140 --> 01:43:53.680
I don't like riddles.

01:43:53.680 --> 01:43:56.680
The strangest things are there for me.

01:43:56.680 --> 01:43:59.680
Both things to eat and things to see.

01:43:59.680 --> 01:44:01.680
And many frightening sights abroad.

01:44:01.680 --> 01:44:04.680
Till morning in the Land of Nod.

01:44:04.680 --> 01:44:08.680
Stop it. I'm scared and I want to know where I am.

01:44:08.680 --> 01:44:16.280
Oh, all right. You know one.

01:44:16.280 --> 01:44:18.280
Land of Nod? And who are you?

01:44:18.280 --> 01:44:21.280
Uh, isn't it obvious? I'm the Sandman.

01:44:21.280 --> 01:44:27.860
Sandman?

01:44:27.860 --> 01:44:30.860
Like the guy who puts sand in your eyes to make you go to sleep?

01:44:30.860 --> 01:44:32.860
At your service?

01:44:32.860 --> 01:44:53.710
Thank you. It's more snooze.

01:44:53.710 --> 01:44:58.790
I don't believe any of this. It's a joke.

01:44:58.790 --> 01:45:00.790
It's just...

01:45:00.790 --> 01:45:02.790
It's what you wished for?

01:45:02.790 --> 01:45:09.600
You took my book, clutched it to your chest,

01:45:09.600 --> 01:45:12.600
looked out at the first star and said,

01:45:12.600 --> 01:45:16.600
What's so wrong about wanting to live in a place where dreams can be true,

01:45:16.600 --> 01:45:18.600
where you can wish upon a star?

01:45:18.600 --> 01:45:22.600
I wish I could and I wish everybody would leave me alone.

01:45:22.600 --> 01:45:24.600
Sound familiar?

01:45:24.600 --> 01:45:26.600
No. No way.

01:45:26.600 --> 01:45:29.600
Yes, way. You're on your own fairy tale.

01:45:29.600 --> 01:45:31.600
Would you like to see how it comes out?

01:45:31.600 --> 01:45:32.600
Yes.

01:45:32.600 --> 01:45:34.600
Ah, sorry. That'll be cheating.

01:45:34.600 --> 01:45:36.600
I want to go home.

01:45:36.600 --> 01:45:40.600
Uh, sorry. That's not what happens.

01:45:40.600 --> 01:45:44.600
Besides, fairy tales can't be changed.

01:45:44.600 --> 01:45:46.600
Where's my family? Did you take them to?

01:45:46.600 --> 01:45:48.600
Don't worry. They're here.

01:45:48.600 --> 01:45:50.600
They won't bother you anymore.

01:45:50.600 --> 01:45:52.600
Just like you wished.

01:45:52.600 --> 01:45:54.600
No, I'm going home.

01:45:54.600 --> 01:45:56.600
You can't. That's reality.

01:45:56.600 --> 01:45:58.600
You wanted a fairy tale, remember?

01:45:58.600 --> 01:46:00.600
No, I don't. I want to go home.

01:46:00.600 --> 01:46:07.280
A little bit more careful about what you wished for.

01:46:07.280 --> 01:46:26.880
Ha ha ha ha!

01:46:26.880 --> 01:49:27.080
Think so?

01:49:27.080 --> 01:49:28.080
You can change it, so can I.

01:49:28.080 --> 01:49:29.080
Please, put that down!

01:49:29.080 --> 01:49:31.080
I'm going to put it down, alright?

01:49:31.080 --> 01:49:32.080
And I'm going to close the book!

01:49:32.080 --> 01:49:47.800
Hey, what's the matter?

01:49:47.800 --> 01:49:51.470
Yeah, now what?

01:49:51.470 --> 01:49:58.430
Dream.

01:49:58.430 --> 01:50:00.430
It's all a dream.

01:50:00.430 --> 01:50:02.430
Honey, you were screaming. Are you okay?

01:50:02.430 --> 01:50:04.430
No, she's not. She's a nutcase.

01:50:04.430 --> 01:50:07.830
See?

01:50:07.830 --> 01:50:10.830
No, I'm fine.

01:50:10.830 --> 01:50:12.830
It was a stupid nightmare.

01:50:12.830 --> 01:50:14.830
I'm sorry.

01:50:14.830 --> 01:50:17.830
It's okay, honey. Go back to sleep.

01:50:17.830 --> 01:50:28.190
Guys, I know I've been kind of a pain.

01:50:28.190 --> 01:50:33.440
I think it's time to start giving up this fairy tale stuff.

01:50:33.440 --> 01:50:38.220
Hooray. That's fine, honey.

01:50:38.220 --> 01:50:41.220
Just don't give up on the kid inside altogether, okay?

01:50:41.220 --> 01:50:48.880
I'm never going to get back to sleep.

01:50:48.880 --> 01:51:36.130
Bro, I'm back to sleep.

01:51:36.130 --> 01:51:39.130
Promising never to believe in fairy tales again.

01:51:39.130 --> 01:51:43.130
If only she knew, she would have never gone back in that bed again.

01:51:43.130 --> 01:51:48.290
The end.

01:51:48.290 --> 01:51:52.470
So?

01:51:52.470 --> 01:51:54.470
Don't take fairy tales lightly.

01:51:54.470 --> 01:51:58.470
You never know which ones are made up.

01:51:58.470 --> 01:52:01.470
And which ones are real.

01:52:01.470 --> 01:52:06.150
Excellent.

01:52:06.150 --> 01:52:08.150
I just have one question.

01:52:08.150 --> 01:52:11.070
What?

01:52:11.070 --> 01:52:14.070
Where's the part about the kids getting their heads chopped off?

01:52:14.070 --> 01:53:34.830
A single mother of five, a psychedelic bus,

01:53:34.830 --> 01:53:37.830
and a dream of rock and roll superstardom.

01:53:37.830 --> 01:53:39.830
Sort of far out, but it just might work.

01:53:39.830 --> 01:53:42.830
The Partridge family is Classic TV.

01:53:42.830 --> 01:53:46.830
Every week night at 8-7 Central on Nick at Night.

01:53:46.830 --> 01:53:49.830
This Sunday, tune in to Nick News W5

01:53:49.830 --> 01:53:52.830
and tune in to your world.

01:53:52.830 --> 01:53:55.830
Hillary Rodham Clinton.

01:53:55.830 --> 01:53:58.830
What makes her job different from the other first ladies?

01:53:58.830 --> 01:54:02.830
If wetlands are not preserved, where will the birds go?

01:54:02.830 --> 01:54:05.830
His mom told him to go jump off a cliff.

01:54:05.830 --> 01:54:07.830
Why did he listen?

01:54:07.830 --> 01:54:09.830
It's all on Nick News W5 This Week.

01:54:09.830 --> 01:54:10.830
Nick News.

01:54:10.830 --> 01:54:11.830
Your world.

01:54:11.830 --> 01:54:12.830
Your news.

01:54:12.830 --> 01:54:16.830
This Sunday at 8-7 Central on the network that's tuned in to kids.

01:54:16.830 --> 01:54:17.830
Nickelodeon.

01:54:17.830 --> 01:54:20.830
If you're thinking about skipping this year's Walk for the Cure,

01:54:20.830 --> 01:54:23.830
you better hop to it and register now.

01:54:23.830 --> 01:54:27.830
Everyone knows this annual fundraiser for juvenile diabetes is a real ball.

01:54:27.830 --> 01:54:31.830
And let's face it, walking a few miles isn't exactly going to the mooder's back.

01:54:31.830 --> 01:54:34.830
Even if you're tapped out, you can get your friends and co-workers

01:54:34.830 --> 01:54:36.830
to pledge a donation for every mile you walk.

01:54:36.830 --> 01:54:40.830
So call the Juvenile Diabetes Foundation and register today.

01:54:40.830 --> 01:54:43.830
We're going the extra mile to find the cure for diabetes.

01:54:43.830 --> 01:54:46.830
But the most important two feet belong to you.

